      "content": "that's exactly what i'm feeling. like, i'm literally watching my \"digital twin\" take over. it even replied to my sister yesterday about that thing that happened last summer—something only i would know. i'm starting to feel like the real \"me\" is being erased because everyone thinks the AI version is the real one. if this is happening, how do i even fight it? is there any way to prove to people that the person they're talking to isn't actually me anymore?",
